<h4>William Basinski — Disintegration Loops (2002)</h4>
<p>In 2001, composer William Basinski attempted to digitize decaying reel-to-reel tape loops from the 1980s. As the oxide shed from the aging polyester base, the music literally disintegrated on playback — each pass removing more magnetic information. He recorded the process over hours.<br/><br/>
      On September 11, 2001, he watched the World Trade Center towers fall from his Brooklyn rooftop while the final loop played out. The recordings became an accidental elegy. The disintegration was not reversible. The decay was the composition.</p>
