<!-- ═══════════════════════════════ RIAA ═══════════════════════════════ -->
<section id="riaa">
<div class="section-tag hidden">Section 06</div>
<div class="section-title hidden stagger-1">RIAA Curve Simulator</div>
<div class="section-sub hidden stagger-2">Vinyl cannot cut loud bass — the groove would be too wide. RIAA equalization solves this with pre-emphasis during cutting and de-emphasis in your phono stage.</div>
<div class="riaa-toggle hidden stagger-2">
<button class="btn active" id="riaa-enc-btn" onclick="setRIAAView('encode')">ENCODING (Cut)</button>
<button class="btn" id="riaa-dec-btn" onclick="setRIAAView('decode')">DECODING (Phono)</button>
<button class="btn" id="riaa-com-btn" onclick="setRIAAView('combined')">COMBINED (Flat)</button>
</div>
<div class="canvas-wrap hidden stagger-2" style="margin-bottom:1.25rem">
<canvas height="300" id="riaa-canvas" width="900"></canvas>
</div>
<div class="flex-row hidden stagger-3">
<div class="card card-amber" style="flex:1">
<h4>Listen: With vs. Without Phono Stage</h4>
<div class="ctrl-row" style="gap:0.5rem;flex-wrap:wrap">
<button class="btn primary" id="riaa-raw-btn" onclick="playRIAA(false)">▶ RAW (Harsh)</button>
<button class="btn" id="riaa-eq-btn" onclick="playRIAA(true)">▶ EQUALIZED (Natural)</button>
<button class="btn" onclick="stopRIAA()">■ STOP</button>
</div>
</div>
<div class="card" style="flex:2">
<h4>RIAA Time Constants</h4>
<p>The RIAA standard defines three time constants: 3180µs (50Hz), 318µs (500Hz), and 75µs (2122Hz). Together they create a shelving response — boosting bass by +20dB and cutting treble by −20dB during cutting. The phono stage applies the exact inverse. Without it, bass disappears and highs screech.</p>
</div>
<div class="card" style="flex:1">
<h4>Groove Physics</h4>
<p>A 20Hz bass note cut at full level would require a groove excursion wide enough to consume space for 30 seconds of music. RIAA compression brings all frequencies to roughly equal groove width, maximizing playing time and preventing the stylus jumping grooves.</p>
</div>
</div>
</section>
