<div class="card" style="flex:2">
<h4>Physical Archaeology</h4>
<p>Every noise type is a fossil record of the vinyl's history. Surface noise tells of humidity and dust. Clicks mark debris impacts. Crackle reveals micro-fractures in the pressing. Warp wow records temperature stress. Inner groove distortion is the mathematical consequence of geometry — the stylus must reproduce the same lateral velocity as the cutting head, but at a smaller radius.</p>
</div>
